title: Kenneth Dokken
text:
Kenneth Dokken (born 10 October 1978) is a <a href="Norwegians">Norwegian</a> football coach and former <a href="association%20football">football</a> <a href="midfielder">midfielder</a>. Dokken is currently the assistant coach of <a href="Eliteserien">Eliteserien</a> club <a href="V%C3%A5lerenga%20Fotball">Vålerenga</a>. He is the son of former Norway international striker <a href="Arne%20Dokken">Arne Dokken</a>, who is currently the assistant manager of Danish club <a href="Aarhus%20Gymnastikforening">AGF</a>.
He is best known for a violent off-the-ball tackle on <a href="Johan%20Arneng">Johan Arneng</a>.
Kenneth Dokken was head coach of <a href="IF%20Birkebeineren">IF Birkebeineren</a>. He was head coach at <a href="Notodden%20FK">Notodden</a> from 2012 to 2019.
